<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,1666,1979]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1703,1727]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is from the combination of 
<emphasis box="[869,934,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">virilis</emphasis>
(virile) and 
<emphasis box="[1078,1145,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">bestia</emphasis>
(animal), referring to the masculine nature of the male spider; masculine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,1666,1979]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1774,1799]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar in body form and presence of a lamella accompanying the embolus to 
<taxonomicName authority="Thorell" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1891" box="[1204,1389,1775,1799]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Colyttus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1204,1297,1775,1799]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Colyttus</emphasis>
Thorell
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the flat protrusion on the front surface of the male chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[958,1057,1811,1835]" captionStart="FIGURES 286–289" captionStartId="61.[151,263,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[161,1403,179,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-52@61.[161,1425,163,1975]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 286–289. Viribestus suyanensis sp. nov. 286 male holotype, dorsal view; 287 male cephalothorax, front view; 288 male left palp, ventral view; 289 male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 286, 1.0 mm; 287–289, 0.2 mm." pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 287</figureCitation>
), the absence of proximal tegular lobe and the forked retrolateral tibial apophysis of the male palp (
<figureCitation box="[882,1042,1847,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 286–289" captionStartId="61.[151,263,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[161,1403,179,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-52@61.[161,1425,163,1975]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 286–289. Viribestus suyanensis sp. nov. 286 male holotype, dorsal view; 287 male cephalothorax, front view; 288 male left palp, ventral view; 289 male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 286, 1.0 mm; 287–289, 0.2 mm." pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 288–289</figureCitation>
). Also differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[1261,1436,1847,1871]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Canama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1261,1356,1847,1871]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Canama</emphasis>
Simon
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Thorell" authorityName="Thorell. Proszy" authorityYear="1892" box="[199,402,1883,1907]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bathippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,313,1883,1907]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Bathippus</emphasis>
Thorell
</taxonomicName>
in the wide carapace (
<figureCitation box="[657,756,1883,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 286–289" captionStartId="61.[151,263,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[161,1403,179,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-52@61.[161,1425,163,1975]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 286–289. Viribestus suyanensis sp. nov. 286 male holotype, dorsal view; 287 male cephalothorax, front view; 288 male left palp, ventral view; 289 male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 286, 1.0 mm; 287–289, 0.2 mm." pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 286</figureCitation>
), the wide palpal bulb (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1181,1883,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 286–289" captionStartId="61.[151,263,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[161,1403,179,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-52@61.[161,1425,163,1975]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 286–289. Viribestus suyanensis sp. nov. 286 male holotype, dorsal view; 287 male cephalothorax, front view; 288 male left palp, ventral view; 289 male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 286, 1.0 mm; 287–289, 0.2 mm." pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 288–289</figureCitation>
), the presence of a flat protrusion on the front surface of the male chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[753,851,1919,1943]" captionStart="FIGURES 286–289" captionStartId="61.[151,263,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[161,1403,179,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-52@61.[161,1425,163,1975]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 286–289. Viribestus suyanensis sp. nov. 286 male holotype, dorsal view; 287 male cephalothorax, front view; 288 male left palp, ventral view; 289 male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 286, 1.0 mm; 287–289, 0.2 mm." pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 287</figureCitation>
), the presence of a lamella right beside the embolus and the forked retrolateral tibial apophysis of the male palp (
<figureCitation box="[829,988,1955,1979]" captionStart="FIGURES 286–289" captionStartId="61.[151,263,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[161,1403,179,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-52@61.[161,1425,163,1975]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 286–289. Viribestus suyanensis sp. nov. 286 male holotype, dorsal view; 287 male cephalothorax, front view; 288 male left palp, ventral view; 289 male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 286, 1.0 mm; 287–289, 0.2 mm." pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 288–289</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
